The paper deals with improving the accuracy of contactless fingerprint identification, which involves image processing and pattern recognition techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the security aspects of fingerprint identification, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms and statistical models, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Finally, the paper presents experimental results and performance evaluation, which are typical of machine learning (cs.LG) research.
